In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water
(2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).
Quarter @Lime{1}(quartered). Roughly chop @Peanuts{1/2%ounce}(roughly chopped).

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce}, cilantro,
@Sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), juice from half the lime, @salt{pinch},
and @pepper{}. Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.
(If chicken is browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover with a lid.)
Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to stovetop over low heat. Add @Tangy Tamarind Sauce{4%ounce},
1/4 cup water, and @Butter{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring, until combined and butter
has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice and slaw between plates in separate sections. Top rice with chicken;
drizzle with sauce and garnish with peanuts. Serve with remaining lime wedges
on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.